text: my name is daisy and i'm an account
manager supporting machine learning core
startups i first came to aws almost
right out of school as an early career
individual it was super important for me
to find a place where i had the
opportunity to progress my career and
learn from folks around me my journey
here started as an inbound demand
generation representative i was
supporting all types and all sizes of
businesses but i really was attracted to
startup companies and how quickly they
were innovating at aws our culture is
very fast-paced and very much like a
startup so it's fun to work with
companies that are growing quickly
innovating quickly failing fast but
growing together it's awesome to work
for an organization that gives us the
autonomy to go and solve challenges for
our customers specifically when
customers come to me and tell me that
they have a product feature request it's
awesome that i get to go work with that
product team and that service team
directly and make those changes that
impact my customer and their end users
one of my favorite memories was actually
during my first interview the first
interviewer was also a female she was
from the midwest like myself and i sat
down and she immediately felt like she
was welcoming me and i could see myself
in her and i could see myself at the
company so that was really important to
me and each and every day i see women in
leadership and folks like myself with
the same background and experiences
excelling and progressing here
